<section id="fs-idm214195744" class="problem-set-a">
<exercise id="fs-idm223995936">
<problem id="fs-idm204047360">
<para id="fs-idm161690464"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68070"/>The comptroller wants to set the standards according to a study done by a consulting firm for a company. The consulting firm used the following assumptions: The machines never break down. Workers never take a break. The material used is perfect. The material arrives on time. No one takes a day off. Workers are well trained. Workers do not make defective units. What kinds of standards are these? Will the workers be motivated to achieve these standards?</para>
